# ================================================================
# count_to_infinity.event
# Minimal 3-node chain designed to trigger count-to-infinity.
#
# Topology:
#   0 --1-- 1 --1-- 2
#
# After convergence (t=100):
#   Node 0: dv[2]=2 via Node 1
#   Node 1: dv[2]=1 direct; dv[0]=1 direct
#   Node 2: dv[0]=2 via Node 1; dv[1]=1 direct
#
# At t=200: DELETE_LINK 1 2
#   Node 1 loses direct link to 2.
#   Node 1 checks neighbors — only Node 0, which still advertises dv[2]=2.
#   Node 1 concludes: "I can reach 2 via 0 at cost 1+2=3"  ← WRONG (loop)
#
# The storm (link latency=1, each round = 1 time unit):
#   t=200  Node 1 sets dv[2]=3,   broadcasts to Node 0
#   t=201  Node 0 sets dv[2]=4,   broadcasts to Node 1
#   t=202  Node 1 sets dv[2]=5,   broadcasts to Node 0
#   ...    increments by 1 each hop until cost >= INFINITY (500)
#   t≈697  both nodes finally mark 2 as unreachable
#
# Expected message count (with split horizon / poison reverse: ~5):
#   Without fix: ~500+ messages just from the loop
# ================================================================

# ── Phase 1: Build topology ──────────────────────────────────────
0 ADD_LINK 0 1 1
0 ADD_LINK 1 2 1

# ── Phase 2: Verify baseline after convergence ───────────────────
100 PRINT Baseline
100 DRAW_PATH 0 2
100 DRAW_PATH 1 2
100 DRAW_TREE 0

# ── Phase 3: Delete link 1-2 — count-to-infinity begins ─────────
200 PRINT Delete_Link_1-2__storm_begins
200 DELETE_LINK 1 2

# Mid-storm snapshot: Node 1 and Node 0 should show inflated dv[2]
# At t=350, ~150 rounds in — expect dv[2] around 150-155
350 PRINT Mid-storm_snapshot
350 DUMP_NODE 0
350 DUMP_NODE 1

# ── Phase 4: After storm settles (t≈697, check at t=900) ─────────
# Node 2 is still in the topology but isolated.
# Correct answer: no path exists from 0→2 or 1→2.
# DV nodes should also report unreachable (dv[2] hit INFINITY=500).
900 PRINT Post-storm
900 DUMP_NODE 0
900 DUMP_NODE 1
